Basetsana Kumalo reflected on the shows legacy as news of it coming to an end dominated social media conversations on Thursday. JOHANNESBURG - Media personality and businesswoman Basetsana Kumalo has confirmed that "Top Billing" has been cancelled. READ: Kumalo tackles controversial 'Our Perfect Wedding' episode The former host took to Twitter on Thursday to reflect on the impact the show has had on South Africans. "#TopBilling is the longest-running entertainment & lifestyle tv show in SA. It’s been an exceptional 25 yrs as a producer & co-owner of Tswelopele Productions, producing a show that has captivated audiences, especially when I think of my 1st day as a presenter on TopBilling", said Kumalo. Kumalo ended her lengthy thread by thanking viewers for tuning into the show for the last 25 years.